title: What tool in your life would you call a secret superpower?
text:
Any thing that makes you feel as though you can "fly". That makes you faster or saves you effort in a way that feels particularly unreal and sublime.

Can be anything human-made, from a piece of software to a well designed gardening tool.

Ask HN: What metaphor did someone use that helped you “grok” something?
text: When I learned swimming as a kid, I struggled with coordinating how my legs were supposed to move. It seemed that I could either focus on my arms, or on one leg, but never on both legs, and much less on arms and legs together. Then my swimming instructor told me, "Move your legs just like a frog". That did it. That one metaphor took all the cognitive overhead away for me. I instantly "got" it.
